A 32-year-old passenger was left injured when a bakkie loaded with bales of fabric veered and overturned on Vincent Dickinson Road near Canelands area in Verulam, on Wednesday afternoon (5 February). Prem Balram, spokesperson of the first responders Reaction Unit South Africa (Rusa), said the incident happened at 1.45pm. He said, “Upon arrival on scene, it was found that the passenger had sustained moderate injuries and was transported to a provincial hospital by ambulance.” Balram stated that according to the witnesses, the bakkie was traveling down to Old Main Road and was unable to stop at the intersection. He said in an attempt to avoid colliding into other vehicles the driver veered off the road causing the bakkie to overturn. Balram added that the driver was not injured.